    "Name": "Kumazemi KUZ-C2",
    "Details": "As the original production variant, the KUZ-C2 carries the heaviest armor allocation of any Kumazemi configuration, reflecting the chassis's garrison-defense roots. Its armament centers on an AC/20 paired with an LRM-15, giving it both heavy direct-fire punch and indirect support capability, while a pair of Medium Lasers and a head-mounted Machine Gun handle close-in defense. CASE installations in both side torsos protect the pilot from the risks of carrying such substantial ammunition reserves\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Rugged</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.14</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Lower, Right Lower</color>",
